{"slug":"sirkuler-25-0070eng","reference":"Sirkuler_25_0070ENG","gazette":"Official Gazette Dated 31 December 2024 and Numbered 32769 4. Duplicate","title":"Communiqué on Import Control of Vehicle Parts (Product Safety and Inspection: 2025/25)","date":"13 Ocak 2025","bodyHtml":"<p><a href=\"https://www.resmigazete.gov.tr/eskiler/2024/12/20241231M4-23.htm\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">The Communiqué on Import Control of Vehicle Parts (Product Safety and Inspection: 2025/25)</a> has been published.</p><p>In the face of technical problems such as taking samples at customs, preparing test samples, shipping the sample or performing tests after assembly in some products during the actual inspections within the scope of the Communiqué, the undertaking in Annex-3 of the Communiqué will be uploaded to TAREKS electronically. Based on the report to be given as a result of the examination of the relevant inspection unit, a TAREKS reference number will be created to indicate that the product can be imported, provided that the conformity inspection is carried out within the period specified in the report. In the event that the conformity audit to be carried out by the relevant inspection unit is negative, this situation will be notified to the importer company and the General Directorate of Product Safety and Inspection of the Ministry in writing.</p><p>Tires in tariff heading 4011 and led bulbs in heading 8539.52 were included in the scope of the communiqué.</p><p>Due to the changes in the annexes to the communiqué, the transition process was regulated.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Transition process</span></p><p>P<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">ROVISIONAL ARTICLE 1</span>- <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">(1) The import of products for which a transport document has been issued to be shipped to Turkey for export in the country of origin before 1/1/2025 or submitted to the customs authorities in accordance with the Customs Legislation, until 28/2/2025 (including this date), upon the request of the importing company, is concluded in accordance with the Communiqué on Import Control of Vehicle Parts (Product Safety and Inspection: 2024/25) repealed by Article 15.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">(2) The provisions of this Communiqué shall not apply until 28/2/2025 (including this date) for the import of products within the scope of HS Codes that are not included in Annex-1 of the Communiqué on Import Control of Vehicle Parts (Product Safety and Inspection: 2024/25), which is included in Annex-1 but repealed by Article 15. This paragraph does not apply to HS Codes that differ due to changes made in the Turkish Customs Tariff Schedul</span>e.</p><table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n <tbody><tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes;height:14.4pt\">\r\n  <td width=\"507\" nowrap=\"\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:380.0pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\r\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:14.4pt\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:0cm;\r\n  line-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-ascii-font-family:\r\n  Aptos;mso-fareast-font-family:Aptos;mso-hansi-font-family:Aptos;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n  Aptos;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none;mso-fareast-language:TR\">NEW\r\n  ITEMS INCLUDED IN THE COMMUNIQUÉ</span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\n  mso-ascii-font-family:Aptos;mso-fareast-font-family:Aptos;mso-hansi-font-family:\r\n  Aptos;mso-bidi-font-family:Aptos;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none;\r\n  mso-fareast-language:TR\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow:1;height:14.4pt\">\r\n  <td width=\"129\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:96.5pt;border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;\r\n  mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;height:14.4